extends ../../layouts/_layout_doc 
block setting
    -var mainActive = 'docs';
    -var slideActive = 'breadcrumb';
    - title = "Component - Breadcrumb"

block content 
    h1.bd-title#content Breadcrumb
    p.bd-lead Indicate the current page’s location within a navigational hierarchy that automatically adds separators via CSS.

    h2 Examples
    .bd-example
        +breadcrumb()        
        +breadcrumb([{'title':'Library'}])
        +breadcrumb([{'title':'Library','link':'#'},{'title':'Data'}])
        +breadcrumb([{'title':'Library Page','link':'#'},{'title':'Data Page','link':'#'},{'title':'Contact Page'}],'Home page')

    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.js.
                +breadcrumb()        
                +breadcrumb([{'title':'Library'}])
                +breadcrumb([{'title':'Library','link':'#'},{'title':'Data'}])
                +breadcrumb([{'title':'Library Page','link':'#'},{'title':'Data Page','link':'#'},{'title':'Contact Page'}],'Home page')

    h2 Changing the separator
    p
        | Separators are automatically added in CSS through 
        a(href='https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/::before')
            code.highlighter-rouge ::before
        |  and 
        a(href='https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/content')
            code.highlighter-rouge content
        | . They can be changed by changing 
        code.highlighter-rouge $breadcrumb-divider
        | . The 
        a(href='https://sass-lang.com/documentation/Sass/Script/Functions.html#quote-instance_method') quote
        |  function is needed to generate the quotes around a string, so if you want 
        <code class="highlighter-rouge">&gt;</code>
        |  as seperator, you can use this:

    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.sass $breadcrumb-divider: quote("&gt;");
    
    p
        | It’s also possible to use a 
        strong base64 embedded SVG icon
        | :

    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.sass $breadcrumb-divider: url(data:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSI4IiBoZWlnaHQ9IjgiPjxwYXRoIGQ9Ik0yLjUgMEwxIDEuNSAzLjUgNCAxIDYuNSAyLjUgOGw0LTQtNC00eiIgZmlsbD0iY3VycmVudENvbG9yIi8+PC9zdmc+);
    
    p
        | The separator can be removed by setting 
        code.highlighter-rouge $breadcrumb-divider
        |  to 
        code.highlighter-rouge none
        | :
    
    figure.highlight
        pre
            code.sass $breadcrumb-divider: none;

    h2 Accessibility

    p
        | Since breadcrumbs provide a navigation, it’s a good idea to add a meaningful label such as 
        code.highlighter-rouge aria-label="breadcrumb"
        |  to describe the type of navigation provided in the 
        code.highlighter-rouge &lt;nav&gt;
        |  element, as well as applying an 
        code.highlighter-rouge aria-current="page"
        |  to the last item of the set to indicate that it represents the current page.

    p
        | For more information, see the 
        a(href='https://www.w3.org/TR/wai-aria-practices/#breadcrumb') WAI-ARIA Authoring Practices for the breadcrumb pattern
        | .